======================================================================
CHANGES for Ice for Android 0.2.0
======================================================================

This file describes the change history for Ice for Android.


======================================================================
Changes since version 0.1.1
======================================================================

- Fixed a NullPointerException in the network tracing code.

- Updated the demos to use the new AMI mapping for Ice 3.4.

- Changed the way the demo and test suite projects locate Ice.jar. It
  is no longer necessary to manually create the ICE_JAR_HOME path
  variable. Instead, the most recent version of the Slice2Java Eclipse
  plug-in creates the ICE_HOME classpath variable automatically, and
  the sample projects now refer to this variable. See the README file
  for details.


======================================================================
Changes since version 0.1.0
======================================================================

- Fixed a bug with connection establishment in the TCP transport.

- Fixed bugs in object adapter shutdown.

- Slice types now implement java.io.Serializable.
